18 schools; economic sectors
19 A. The legislature finds and declares that:
20 (1) Economic development and the economic vitality of the state are
21 dependent upon an educated and highly trained workforce.
22 (2) Manufacturing, industrial, technology, energy, utility, and other
23 sectors are all dependent on a workforce that has vocational training and
24 technical education.
25 (3) High-quality educational options that include vocational and
26 technical educations are essential to the academic growth of Louisiana's
27 students and the ability of the state to attract businesses, maintain a highly
28 talented workforce, and expand existing businesses.
